  stimulus_text = 'The use of semicolons is particularly important in separating independent clauses—clauses that could stand alone as sentences—when a conjunction is not used. This is important for clarity, as semicolons help to avoid run-on sentences, but they also help the reader to understand how the ideas in the text are related. Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
